6
00:02:08,375 --> 00:02:11,139
[Child Laughing]

7
00:02:14,981 --> 00:02:18,576
[Phone Ringing]

8
00:02:20,187 --> 00:02:21,950
[Rings]

9
00:02:23,757 --> 00:02:25,725
[Rings]

10
00:02:29,796 --> 00:02:32,594
- Sí. Bueno.
- [Man On Phone] Family is everything.

11
00:02:32,699 --> 00:02:34,496
No?

12
00:02:34,601 --> 00:02:38,002
Now, do you love your son?

13
00:02:38,972 --> 00:02:42,738
- Sí.
- [Men Shouting]

14
00:02:45,011 --> 00:02:47,411
- [Man Shouting]
- [Groaning]

15
00:02:49,616 --> 00:02:54,212
Now... do you understand?

16
00:02:54,354 --> 00:02:58,723
You have a $ 10 million insurance policy.
I know that.

17
00:02:58,825 --> 00:03:03,353
[Speaking Spanish]

18
00:03:22,148 --> 00:03:25,015
- [Horns Honking]
- [Man Shouting]

19
00:03:28,522 --> 00:03:30,513
[Tires Screeching]

20
00:03:32,759 --> 00:03:36,456
[Shouting]

21
00:03:39,032 --> 00:03:42,729
[Crying]

22
00:04:21,575 --> 00:04:24,135
- [Woman Squealing]
- [Chattering In Spanish]

23
00:04:31,551 --> 00:04:33,781
[Man Shouts In Spanish]

24
00:04:39,926 --> 00:04:42,690
[Angry Shouting]

25
00:04:54,641 --> 00:04:57,508
[Woman Yelling In Spanish]

26
00:05:02,449 --> 00:05:04,974
[Chattering In Spanish]

27
00:05:05,118 --> 00:05:08,053
[Mariachi Band]

28
00:05:08,154 --> 00:05:10,247
Georgina!

29
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:13,655
Obey me, I will love you.
Come on.

30
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,523
That's how it works, huh?

31
00:05:15,629 --> 00:05:18,792
- Simple.
- That's right.

32
00:05:18,898 --> 00:05:20,798
Mwah.

33
00:05:24,938 --> 00:05:28,237
She got a sister?

34
00:05:28,341 --> 00:05:31,538
How's business?

35
00:05:31,645 --> 00:05:34,546
TheJapanese are here in a big way.

36
00:05:35,982 --> 00:05:38,473
Cheap labor, factory space.

37
00:05:38,618 --> 00:05:42,554
But they feel a lot safer living
over the border in El Paso.

38
00:05:42,689 --> 00:05:45,715
I ferry them back and forth.
They think I'm John Wayne.

39
00:05:45,859 --> 00:05:47,759
- Ah.
- Come on.

40
00:05:47,861 --> 00:05:52,127
[Men Singing In Spanish]

41
00:05:52,232 --> 00:05:55,463
- I live like a king down here.
- Yes, you do.

42
00:05:59,205 --> 00:06:02,299
- You been workin'?
- Yeah. No.

43
00:06:02,409 --> 00:06:04,468
Nah. Been movin' around,
you know.

44
00:06:04,577 --> 00:06:08,638
Colombia, couple of places I can't name.
Nothing catches my fancy.

45
00:06:10,517 --> 00:06:13,509
Oh.

46
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:16,145
You think God will forgive us
for what we've done?

47
00:06:16,289 --> 00:06:18,814
- No.
- You don't?

48
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:23,122
Me either.

49
00:06:23,229 --> 00:06:28,030
- How long you staying?
- I don't know. I just... you know.

50
00:06:28,134 --> 00:06:32,093
I wanted to see you, Ray,
see how you're doin'.

51
00:06:32,205 --> 00:06:34,730
You know, I came by on impulse.

52
00:06:34,841 --> 00:06:38,402
Well, I could do with some impulse.

53
00:06:48,555 --> 00:06:51,547
What happened?

54
00:06:51,691 --> 00:06:53,886
Family paid the ransom...

55
00:06:53,993 --> 00:06:57,986
then they sent the kid home
after a couple of days...

56
00:06:58,098 --> 00:07:00,259
minus an ear, of course.

57
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:03,929
Now every mother in Mexico City
with a little bit of money wants
bigger and better bodyguards...

58
00:07:04,037 --> 00:07:06,005
my own wife included.

59
00:07:06,106 --> 00:07:09,405
I hate to break it to you,
but she's right. She's right.

60
00:07:11,111 --> 00:07:15,377
Look, Sammy, all my clients have, uh,
kidnap and ransom insurance.

61
00:07:15,482 --> 00:07:18,713
I have a policy. A.I.G.
My dad gave it to me.

62
00:07:18,852 --> 00:07:22,117
Yeah, I know.
I got it for your dad.

63
00:07:22,222 --> 00:07:25,157
But what are you gonna do in 60 days
when you can't renew it?

64
00:07:25,258 --> 00:07:29,524
- You can't because
you don't have a bodyguard.
- I had to let Emilio go.

65
00:07:29,629 --> 00:07:33,258
You gotta please Lisa.
I mean, hey, ass like that's hard to find.

66
00:07:35,702 --> 00:07:39,968
Look, a bodyguard's
like anything else.

67
00:07:40,073 --> 00:07:43,338
You get what you pay for, okay?

68
00:07:43,443 --> 00:07:46,435
You could do this.
You get one that's got a decent résumé.

69
00:07:46,546 --> 00:07:48,878
We're not looking for
goddamn Superman here, right?

70
00:07:48,982 --> 00:07:51,712
Get someone cheap
till you renew the policy...

71
00:07:51,851 --> 00:07:55,218
and then, uh...
then fire the prick for whatever.

72
00:07:55,321 --> 00:07:57,346
Incompetence.

73
00:07:57,490 --> 00:08:01,824
All kidding aside, the most important thing
is that your daughter goes back to school...

74
00:08:01,928 --> 00:08:04,897
and that your wife gets to save face.

75
00:08:04,998 --> 00:08:09,799
This way, you won't be the only
unprotected family in the neighborhood.

76
00:08:22,415 --> 00:08:25,612
That's right. A bodyguard.
Your Spanish is good enough.

77
00:08:25,752 --> 00:08:29,153
- You're crazy.
- You even look the part.

78
00:08:29,255 --> 00:08:31,723
In my state,
I couldn't guard a corpse.

79
00:08:31,825 --> 00:08:34,623
It's rich guys flashing their cash.
It's all for show.

80
00:08:34,727 --> 00:08:39,858
- Nothing's gonna happen.
- Yeah? You think they'd hire
a drunk, a has-been?

81
00:08:41,534 --> 00:08:44,833
You have to keep it under control.

82
00:08:44,938 --> 00:08:49,705
What if there was, you know, say,
a kidnapping attempt? What do I do then?

83
00:08:49,809 --> 00:08:53,836
You do your best. They're not gonna be
paying you enough to perform miracles.

84
00:08:53,947 --> 00:08:56,541
- I don't know.
- It's not exactly a scam, Crease.

85
00:08:56,649 --> 00:09:00,813
- Even at half speed, you're pretty damn good.
- Yeah.

86
00:09:00,954 --> 00:09:03,115
Bodyguard's gotta be close
to people though.

87
00:09:03,256 --> 00:09:06,089
He gotta talk all the time,
and I'm no good at that.

88
00:09:06,192 --> 00:09:09,719
You'll be the silent type.
People are gonna appreciate that.

89
00:09:09,829 --> 00:09:13,230
[Laughing]

90
00:09:16,669 --> 00:09:19,536
Bodyguard. So who's the guy?

91
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:22,540
Samuel Ramos. He's a young guy.

92
00:09:22,642 --> 00:09:25,440
He owns one of the plants in Juárez.

93
00:09:25,545 --> 00:09:27,479
Yeah?

94
00:09:27,580 --> 00:09:30,378
TheJap car industry is in the toilet.

95
00:09:30,516 --> 00:09:33,451
He's trying to persuade Ford
to partner with him.

96
00:09:33,553 --> 00:09:37,421
I think he's in trouble.
His family lives in Mexico City.

97
00:09:37,523 --> 00:09:40,014
He asked me if I knew
anybody he could trust.

98
00:09:41,628 --> 00:09:44,620
- And you thought of me.
- Yeah.

99
00:09:44,731 --> 00:09:48,132
Take a job, Crease.
Breathe some air.

100
00:09:48,234 --> 00:09:50,600
Then decide if you want
to stick around or not.

101
00:09:50,703 --> 00:09:54,799
Besides, I'm glad to see you.
I got nobody to talk to down here.

102
00:10:02,282 --> 00:10:05,183
Listen, my wife wants someone
presentable and polite.

103
00:10:07,587 --> 00:10:11,079
You'll be the fifth candidate
she sees this week.

104
00:10:11,224 --> 00:10:12,953
Your résumé's quite impressive.

105
00:10:13,059 --> 00:10:17,519
Sixteen years of military experience,
extensive counterterrorism work.

106
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:21,191
I'm surprised anybody could afford you.
What's the catch?

107
00:10:21,301 --> 00:10:23,565
I drink.

108
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:25,661
How does that affect you?

109
00:10:25,772 --> 00:10:28,240
Well...

110
00:10:28,341 --> 00:10:30,468
coordination, reaction time.

111
00:10:30,576 --> 00:10:34,342
If top professionals try to kidnap
your daughter, I'll do the best I can...

112
00:10:34,447 --> 00:10:37,473
but the service will be
on par with the pay.

113
00:10:38,651 --> 00:10:40,642
What if amateurs tried?

114
00:10:40,787 --> 00:10:43,881
I'd probably kill 'em.
Is that likely?

115
00:10:44,023 --> 00:10:45,991
No.

116
00:10:46,092 --> 00:10:48,856
No one is to know about your drinking.
That includes my wife.

117
00:11:00,039 --> 00:11:03,270
[Piano]

118
00:11:15,722 --> 00:11:18,486
- [Door Opens]
- [Samuel] Lisa!

119
00:11:20,693 --> 00:11:22,593
Lisa!

120
00:11:22,695 --> 00:11:25,858
[TV: People Chanting]

121
00:11:33,806 --> 00:11:36,707
My wife, Lisa.
And this is John Creasy.

122
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:45,980
- You're an American.
- So are you.

123
00:11:48,054 --> 00:11:49,851
It's all in there.

124
00:11:52,892 --> 00:11:54,826
Would you like a drink?

125
00:11:54,927 --> 00:11:57,657
Yes, uh, Jack and water'd be good.

126
00:11:59,232 --> 00:12:02,690
- Have you done much
of this kind of work before?
- No, ma'am.

127
00:12:02,802 --> 00:12:06,568
But he has a lot of experience
in related fields.

128
00:12:09,075 --> 00:12:11,771
- You have a family, Mr. Creasy?
- No.

129
00:12:11,878 --> 00:12:14,073
Pita.

130
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:16,148
Pita.

131
00:12:17,517 --> 00:12:19,576
- [Creasy] Thank you.
- Yes, Mom?

132
00:12:19,719 --> 00:12:21,619
Honey, this is, uh, Mr. Creasy.

133
00:12:23,256 --> 00:12:26,692
[Speaking Spanish]

134
00:12:26,793 --> 00:12:29,261
In English, honey.

135
00:12:29,362 --> 00:12:31,990
Um, do you wanna show
Mr. Creasy to his room?

136
00:12:32,098 --> 00:12:35,795
- This way, Mr. Creasy.
- Okay.

137
00:12:43,810 --> 00:12:46,210
Thank you.

138
00:12:53,186 --> 00:12:55,984
Just like that?

139
00:12:56,089 --> 00:12:58,489
I think it's nice...

140
00:12:58,591 --> 00:13:00,991
that he's an American.

141
00:13:01,094 --> 00:13:05,292
I think it's terrific. You sure?

142
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:10,265
Thank you.

143
00:13:10,369 --> 00:13:12,997
Thank you.

144
00:13:13,106 --> 00:13:15,574
I feel better now.

145
00:13:17,477 --> 00:13:20,378
- ¡: Hola, Bruno!
- ¡: Buenas tardes!

146
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,778
That's Bruno, the gardener.

147
00:13:22,882 --> 00:13:24,941
And, um, that's Maria, the cook.

148
00:13:25,084 --> 00:13:27,848
- ¡: Hola, Maria!
- Hola, Pita.

149
00:13:30,156 --> 00:13:34,149
We fixed the room up two weeks ago.
It's nicer than before.

150
00:13:37,363 --> 00:13:41,197
You've got a TVand C.D. player.
What kind of music do you like, Mr. Creasy?

151
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,666
I don't know.

152
00:13:43,769 --> 00:13:46,260
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

153
00:13:46,372 --> 00:13:49,535
- [Parrot Squawks]
- That's Bird.

154
00:13:49,642 --> 00:13:52,509
Emilio forgot to take him
when he left.

155
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:56,011
Emilio was my last bodyguard.

156
00:13:58,050 --> 00:14:02,180
Have you protected a lot of children
before, Mr. Creasy?

157
00:14:02,321 --> 00:14:05,085
Creasy. You can call me Creasy.
And no, you're the first.

158
00:14:05,191 --> 00:14:07,091
Creasy.

159
00:14:07,193 --> 00:14:09,127
Bye, Creasy.

160
00:14:09,228 --> 00:14:11,890
So long.

161
00:14:12,999 --> 00:14:14,728
Bye, Bird.

162
00:14:14,834 --> 00:14:17,598
- [Squawks]
- [Door Closes]

163
00:14:19,405 --> 00:14:21,737
Ow.

164
00:14:24,710 --> 00:14:28,202
- School tomorrow, peeps.
- Does that mean we can get a dog?

165
00:14:29,615 --> 00:14:32,106
Dad promised me one
when I went back to school.

166
00:14:32,218 --> 00:14:33,879
Yeah, we'll see.

167
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:37,820
If you get a dog,
will you give up your bear?

168
00:14:37,924 --> 00:14:41,257
You're getting too old for him.

169
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:44,761
- How'd you like Mr. Creasy?
- Creasy.

170
00:14:44,864 --> 00:14:47,230
He said to call him just Creasy.

171
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,801
- Uh-huh.
- That isn't disrespectful, is it?

172
00:14:49,902 --> 00:14:52,200
No, not if he asked you.

173
00:14:52,305 --> 00:14:55,138
Here. There you go.

174
00:14:57,276 --> 00:15:00,439
[Sighs]

175
00:15:02,915 --> 00:15:06,715
- He's like a bear too.
- Yeah?

176
00:15:06,852 --> 00:15:09,150
A big, sad bear.

177
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:14,419
- Is he sad?
- I think. Or something.

178
00:15:18,231 --> 00:15:20,131
- Good night, honey.
- Night.

179
00:15:23,569 --> 00:15:26,834
- Oh, can you get me
some floss in the morning?
- Floss?

180
00:15:26,939 --> 00:15:30,466
- Yeah, the strawberry kind.
- Oh, sure.

181
00:15:32,812 --> 00:15:34,837
Good night, Bear.

182
00:15:35,948 --> 00:15:37,916
Creasy Bear.

183
00:15:39,118 --> 00:15:41,678
[Sighs]

184
00:15:46,392 --> 00:15:48,360
[Squawks]

185
00:16:01,274 --> 00:16:11,450
[Skipped item nr. 185]

186
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:13,748
What's that one for?

187
00:16:13,886 --> 00:16:15,786
La Virgin de Guadalupe.

188
00:16:15,888 --> 00:16:20,291
Business. For Toyota, for Ford.

189
00:16:20,393 --> 00:16:23,021
If one dies, maybe she can
resurrect the other one.

190
00:16:23,129 --> 00:16:25,689
I don't know.

191
00:16:25,798 --> 00:16:28,733
- [Sighs]
- She likes him.

192
00:16:30,436 --> 00:16:33,633
- What are you talking about?
- Creasy.

193
00:16:35,174 --> 00:16:37,836
Pita likes him.

194
00:16:37,943 --> 00:16:39,843
Pita loves school.

195
00:16:39,945 --> 00:16:45,144
Pita would love Count Dracula
ifhe took her back there, honey.

196
00:16:45,284 --> 00:16:47,252
Okay?

197
00:16:49,722 --> 00:16:52,589
- Hey. Are you okay?
- I don't know.

198
00:16:52,692 --> 00:16:56,788
- Okay?
- [Sighs]

199
00:16:56,896 --> 00:16:59,330
I don't know, Lisa.

200
00:16:59,432 --> 00:17:01,332
I'm trying.

201
00:17:26,125 --> 00:17:28,821
[Bell Tolling]

202
00:17:38,804 --> 00:17:42,433
[Squawking]

203
00:17:48,347 --> 00:17:51,339
[Squawking Continues]

204
00:17:56,589 --> 00:17:58,557
Come on, Bird.

205
00:17:58,657 --> 00:18:01,956
That's right.
That's right. Come on.

206
00:18:02,061 --> 00:18:05,224
All right. Home to Emilio.

207
00:18:05,331 --> 00:18:08,198
You're home free, baby.

208
00:18:11,203 --> 00:18:14,695
[Horns Honking]

209
00:18:28,354 --> 00:18:31,118
- Where are you from, Creasy?
- The U.S.

210
00:18:31,223 --> 00:18:34,158
- I know, but which state?
- No state in particular.

211
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:36,251
You can drive and talk
at the same time.

212
00:18:36,362 --> 00:18:38,830
No, I can't, Pita, so, please,
let me just do my job.

213
00:18:42,134 --> 00:18:45,001
Are you going to stay?

214
00:18:45,104 --> 00:18:47,004
My last bodyguard left.

215
00:18:47,106 --> 00:18:49,973
Somebody gave him
more money than we could.

216
00:18:50,075 --> 00:18:54,034
I guess that makes me
a bargain then, huh?

217
00:18:54,146 --> 00:18:58,549
Being black... is that a positive or negative
for a bodyguard in Mexico?

218
00:18:58,684 --> 00:19:00,515
Time will tell.

219
00:19:04,056 --> 00:19:08,288
There were 24 kidnappings
in Mexico City in the last six days.

220
00:19:08,394 --> 00:19:10,294
- Four a day.
- Yeah?

221
00:19:10,396 --> 00:19:12,864
- Twenty-four?
- Twenty-four. What do you
think about that, Creasy?

222
00:19:12,965 --> 00:19:16,628
- I think that you know
entirely more than you should.
- Well, thank you.

223
00:19:25,144 --> 00:19:28,204
[Bell Tolling]

224
00:19:28,314 --> 00:19:31,215
[Chattering]

225
00:19:39,792 --> 00:19:42,420
[Girl]
Hola, Miguel.

226
00:19:44,964 --> 00:19:46,829
- See you later.
- You have to sign.

227
00:19:46,932 --> 00:19:51,232
- What?
- You have to sign in, show them your I.D.

228
00:19:51,337 --> 00:19:54,773
Buenos días. Come on.

229
00:19:55,941 --> 00:19:57,841
Right there.

230
00:19:57,943 --> 00:20:00,571
- Hola, Manuel.
- Hola, Pita.

231
00:20:11,390 --> 00:20:13,290
- ¡: Hola, Pita!
- ¡: Hola!

232
00:20:13,392 --> 00:20:17,590
Pita! It's so good to have you back.

233
00:20:17,696 --> 00:20:20,597
Sister Anna, this is
my new bodyguard, Creasy.

234
00:20:20,699 --> 00:20:23,827
Sister Anna, the headmistress.

235
00:20:23,936 --> 00:20:25,961
- Señor Creasy.
- [Bell Rings]

236
00:20:26,071 --> 00:20:27,971
Hurry. Class is about to begin.

237
00:20:28,073 --> 00:20:30,405
- Go, go.
- Bye, Creasy.

238
00:20:30,509 --> 00:20:33,000
- Madre.
- You must look after our Pita.

239
00:20:33,112 --> 00:20:35,307
It is not good that she's late today.

240
00:20:35,414 --> 00:20:39,976
I'm very sorry. I, uh... I'll have to get
used to the rules. It won't happen again.

241
00:20:40,119 --> 00:20:43,646
No offense, but I regret
that your profession needs to exist.

242
00:20:43,789 --> 00:20:46,917
[Chuckles]
So do I, Madre. So do I.

243
00:20:47,026 --> 00:20:50,985
Do you ever see the hand of God
in what you do?

244
00:20:52,598 --> 00:20:54,725
No, not for a long time.

245
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:58,200
The Bible says,
"Be not overcome of evil, but overcome..."

246
00:20:58,304 --> 00:21:01,671
"Overcome evil with good."

247
00:21:01,774 --> 00:21:04,607
