- What do you know about him?
About Fuentes?
- [Exhales]

983
01:35:56,130 --> 01:35:59,531
Three years ago they caught him with $50,000
and a dead body in the trunk of his car.

984
01:35:59,634 --> 01:36:01,261
- Huh.
- Never charged.

985
01:36:01,369 --> 01:36:04,236
Arresting officer couldn't testify
'cause he was dead.

986
01:36:05,840 --> 01:36:08,240
- Is he La Hermandad?
- Mm-hmm.

987
01:36:08,376 --> 01:36:11,868
- You know where he lives?
- He lives in a judicial compound.

988
01:36:13,848 --> 01:36:16,749
He travels by motorcade.

989
01:36:20,121 --> 01:36:22,487
Creasy, he's better protected
than the president of Mexico.

990
01:36:22,590 --> 01:36:24,854
He's gonna need it.
You gonna take care of her?

991
01:36:24,959 --> 01:36:27,484
- Yes. Well, how can I find you?
- I'll find you.

992
01:36:53,287 --> 01:36:55,187
[Phone Ringing]

993
01:36:55,289 --> 01:36:59,225
This is my jurisdiction.

994
01:36:59,327 --> 01:37:03,661
I want this man as much as Creasy does.

995
01:37:03,764 --> 01:37:08,827
He'll deliver more justice in a weekend
than 10 years of your courts and tribunals.

996
01:37:08,936 --> 01:37:12,269
- Just stay out of his way.
- I plan to. [Sniffs]

997
01:37:19,747 --> 01:37:23,183
I will even help him, if I can.

998
01:37:23,317 --> 01:37:27,481
But, uh, I would like to
understand him.

999
01:37:29,323 --> 01:37:30,984
Give me that.

1000
01:37:31,092 --> 01:37:33,720
Pita Ramos...

1001
01:37:35,296 --> 01:37:37,196
that's a number to you.

1002
01:37:37,298 --> 01:37:42,235
You know, one more dead,
but a number.

1003
01:37:42,336 --> 01:37:44,930
What was she to Creasy then?

1004
01:37:45,039 --> 01:37:47,872
She showed him
it was all right to live again.

1005
01:37:51,045 --> 01:37:55,072
And the kidnappers
took that away, huh?

1006
01:37:55,216 --> 01:37:59,175
And they're gonna wish
they never touched a hair on her head.

1007
01:38:00,688 --> 01:38:03,885
A man can be an artist...

1008
01:38:06,794 --> 01:38:09,422
in anything... food, whatever.

1009
01:38:09,530 --> 01:38:14,092
It depends on how good he is at it.

1010
01:38:17,505 --> 01:38:19,405
Creasy's art is death.

1011
01:38:22,310 --> 01:38:26,110
He's about to paint his masterpiece.

1012
01:38:33,487 --> 01:38:35,955
I don't have anything else to say.

1013
01:38:37,425 --> 01:38:39,484
[TVReporter: Spanish]

1014
01:39:01,983 --> 01:39:04,281
[Spanish]

1015
01:39:58,506 --> 01:40:00,406
[Knocking]

1016
01:40:04,612 --> 01:40:07,240
Shh. Shh.
[Spanish]

1017
01:40:09,617 --> 01:40:13,576
- [Siren Chirps]
- [Engines Starting]

1018
01:40:22,963 --> 01:40:25,693
[Spanish]

1019
01:40:25,800 --> 01:40:28,132
Forgiveness is between them and God.

1020
01:40:28,235 --> 01:40:31,136
It's my job to arrange the meeting.

1021
01:40:56,197 --> 01:40:58,757
[Chirping]

1022
01:42:19,480 --> 01:42:22,643
[Fuentes Shouting In Spanish]

1023
01:42:27,488 --> 01:42:30,218
Don't move.
Put your hands down. Put 'em down.

1024
01:42:30,324 --> 01:42:32,417
[Tires Screeching]

1025
01:42:38,933 --> 01:42:41,561
- [Beep]
- [Man] SeñorJohn W. Creasy...

1026
01:42:41,669 --> 01:42:45,161
is under arrest for the murder
of two officers of theJudicial Police.

1027
01:42:45,272 --> 01:42:47,172
[Distorted Scream]

1028
01:42:47,308 --> 01:42:50,368
He's suspected
of possible involvement...

1029
01:42:50,511 --> 01:42:53,947
of possible involvement in
the kidnapping of Lupita Ramos.

1030
01:42:54,081 --> 01:42:56,208
- [Helicopter Blades Whirring]
- [Man On Radio, Indistinct]

1031
01:42:58,319 --> 01:43:00,753
[Car Horn Honking]

1032
01:43:07,795 --> 01:43:10,855
[Man On Radio, Indistinct]

1033
01:43:23,944 --> 01:43:26,742
Can you hear me? Huh?

1034
01:43:28,382 --> 01:43:30,350
Know where we are?

1035
01:43:31,585 --> 01:43:35,954
We're under the bridge
where the deal went bad.

1036
01:43:36,056 --> 01:43:40,823
The ransom got stolen.
You wanna tell me what happened?

1037
01:43:40,928 --> 01:43:43,590
- Have you heard of La Hermandad?
- Yes, I have.

1038
01:43:43,697 --> 01:43:45,597
- Do you know what it is?
- Yes.

1039
01:43:45,699 --> 01:43:47,826
I'm the president of La Hermandad.

1040
01:43:47,935 --> 01:43:49,630
- You're the president?
- Yes.

1041
01:43:49,737 --> 01:43:51,830
The president? Wow.

1042
01:43:51,939 --> 01:43:53,998
Look at me.

1043
01:43:55,309 --> 01:43:57,709
Oh, you can't.
[Chuckles] I'm sorry.

1044
01:43:57,811 --> 01:43:59,836
- How's that?
- [Grunts]

1045
01:44:08,355 --> 01:44:10,323
Let me show you what I got here.

1046
01:44:12,259 --> 01:44:15,786
See this? This is a charger. It's used
by convicts to hide money and drugs.

1047
01:44:15,896 --> 01:44:19,593
They stick it in their body.
They tuck it up their rectum.

1048
01:44:19,700 --> 01:44:22,931
You familiar with that?
This... Look at me.

1049
01:44:23,037 --> 01:44:25,801
Pencil detonator.

1050
01:44:25,906 --> 01:44:29,637
Timer, used as a receiver-transmitter.

1051
01:44:29,777 --> 01:44:32,769
C-4. Highly explosive.

1052
01:44:32,913 --> 01:44:35,143
You put 'em all together,
you got a bomb.

1053
01:44:35,249 --> 01:44:37,809
Not very sophisticated,
but very powerful.

1054
01:44:40,020 --> 01:44:42,648
- That's what you have in your ass right now.
- [Gasps]

1055
01:44:42,756 --> 01:44:46,123
Don't move. Don't move.
Don't move.

1056
01:44:50,397 --> 01:44:52,865
Cheap watch. Pager watch.

1057
01:44:52,967 --> 01:44:58,599
Used to send a page to the receiver
that's up your behind right now.

1058
01:44:58,706 --> 01:45:01,834
So, I'm gonna send you a page...

1059
01:45:01,976 --> 01:45:03,876
which you will receive...

1060
01:45:07,047 --> 01:45:09,515
in five minutes.

1061
01:45:09,650 --> 01:45:11,880
Now.

1062
01:45:11,986 --> 01:45:14,113
- [Tape Rewinding]
- [Button Clicks]

1063
01:45:16,724 --> 01:45:19,124
You got less than five minutes
to tell me what went down...

1064
01:45:19,226 --> 01:45:22,354
between your men and the kidnapper.

1065
01:45:22,463 --> 01:45:24,294
I have nothing to do with the kidnapper.

1066
01:45:24,398 --> 01:45:27,026
- Four minutes and 30 seconds.
- Nothing. I don't know him.

1067
01:45:27,134 --> 01:45:30,831
You don't know?
Four minutes and 25 seconds.

1068
01:45:32,973 --> 01:45:34,964
Four minutes and 20 seconds.
Are you sure?

1069
01:45:37,845 --> 01:45:40,712
Okay.

1070
01:45:40,814 --> 01:45:44,045
I got all the time in the world.
You don't, but I do.

1071
01:45:44,151 --> 01:45:46,915
- Hey, relax, relax, buddy.
- I'm relaxed.

1072
01:45:47,021 --> 01:45:49,888
You got three minutes, 59 seconds.

1073
01:45:49,990 --> 01:45:52,754
I saw the opportunity,
and I got lucky.

1074
01:45:52,860 --> 01:45:54,350
And?

1075
01:45:54,461 --> 01:45:57,555
And I had my men ready as we
got instructions where to go.

1076
01:45:57,665 --> 01:45:59,599
You had your men ready
to steal the drop.

1077
01:45:59,700 --> 01:46:02,066
You had your men ready to kill
one of the kidnappers, yeah?

1078
01:46:02,169 --> 01:46:04,694
You've done this many times.

1079
01:46:06,607 --> 01:46:09,906
- One of the nephews of the head kidnapper...
- Bingo. Bingo. Bingo.

1080
01:46:10,044 --> 01:46:13,070
- Bingo, yeah. You've done this
many times, huh?
- Many times, yeah.

1081
01:46:13,213 --> 01:46:16,546
- Yeah. Killed many victims too, haven't you?
- Come on, sir.

1082
01:46:16,650 --> 01:46:19,619
- We just make out as best we can.
- "As best we could"?

1083
01:46:19,720 --> 01:46:21,813
[Sighs]

1084
01:46:22,690 --> 01:46:25,784
Two minutes, 47 seconds.

1085
01:46:27,261 --> 01:46:30,526
Wait-Wait a minute. Come on.

1086
01:46:30,631 --> 01:46:32,895
- I have a little gift for you.
- For me?

1087
01:46:33,000 --> 01:46:35,798
- Yeah. Come on. Come on.
- What do you got?

1088
01:46:35,903 --> 01:46:40,033
There was no $ 10 million.
There was one half in the bags.

1089
01:46:40,140 --> 01:46:42,870
The ransom was $10 million?
They put it in two bags.

1090
01:46:43,010 --> 01:46:45,103
- Five million in each bag, right?
- Two bags, true.

1091
01:46:45,245 --> 01:46:48,737
But one has half paper...

1092
01:46:48,882 --> 01:46:51,976
the other only paper.
[Chuckles]

1093
01:46:52,086 --> 01:46:55,988
Maybe your men stole it.

1094
01:46:56,090 --> 01:46:58,581
Whoever did it
took it before the exchange.

1095
01:47:00,561 --> 01:47:03,530
Okay. At the Ramos house...

1096
01:47:03,630 --> 01:47:08,260
before the exchange,
who put the bags in the car?

1097
01:47:08,368 --> 01:47:10,632
- Guess what.
- What?

1098
01:47:10,738 --> 01:47:14,037
Ramos lawyer, Jordan Kalfus.

1099
01:47:14,174 --> 01:47:16,642
- Jordan Kalfus?
- Yeah.

1100
01:47:19,279 --> 01:47:21,747
Pedro.

1101
01:47:29,022 --> 01:47:31,513
Sir? Please.

1102
01:47:31,625 --> 01:47:34,321
l-I'm sorry.
I'm really sorry for the girl.

1103
01:47:34,428 --> 01:47:38,421
It was just business.
You know, I'm a professional.

1104
01:47:38,532 --> 01:47:41,831
That's what everybody keeps saying.
"I'm just a professional."

1105
01:47:41,935 --> 01:47:44,733
Everybody keeps saying that to me.
"I'm just a professional. I'm just a professional."

1106
01:47:44,838 --> 01:47:47,864
I'm getting sick and tired of hearing that.
You understand me?

1107
01:47:51,311 --> 01:47:54,246
What are you going to do now?

1108
01:47:54,348 --> 01:47:56,475
What am I gonna do?
I'm gonna leave. I gotta go.

1109
01:47:56,583 --> 01:47:59,746
- Yeah. I got...
- Come on. Come on. What about me, huh?

1110
01:47:59,853 --> 01:48:02,754
- What about you? You got 40 seconds.
- Come on.

1111
01:48:02,856 --> 01:48:07,293
- Thirty-five.
- A last wish, please. Please.

1112
01:48:07,394 --> 01:48:12,627
Last wish?
I wish you had more time.

1113
01:48:12,733 --> 01:48:16,829
- [Beeping]
- Hey! Hey, hey!

1114
01:48:17,905 --> 01:48:21,432
- [Beeping Increases]
- [Muttering]

1115
01:48:32,586 --> 01:48:37,785
[Woman Singing Indistinctly]

1116
01:49:24,838 --> 01:49:27,636
[Woman Speaking Spanish]

1117
01:49:54,601 --> 01:49:57,229
[Machine Whirring]

1118
01:50:02,376 --> 01:50:04,640
[Woman Continues]

1119
01:50:19,393 --> 01:50:23,022
- [Phone Ringing]
- Hola.

1120
01:50:23,130 --> 01:50:25,758
- Mariana, it's me.
- Creasy, where are you?

1121
01:50:25,866 --> 01:50:28,528
Listen, I got something
that looks like banking codes...

1122
01:50:28,635 --> 01:50:30,500
from BankCoast in the Cayman Islands.

1123
01:50:30,604 --> 01:50:33,732
- I need it translated as fast as you can.
- Whose account is it?

1124
01:50:33,874 --> 01:50:37,935
Jordan Kalfus, and it looks like
U.S. deposits and withdrawals.

1125
01:50:38,078 --> 01:50:40,012
Give me the same thing
on Samuel Ramos.

1126
01:50:40,113 --> 01:50:43,844
Samuel Ramos. That's it?

1127
01:50:43,951 --> 01:50:45,680
- That's it.
- Okay.

1128
01:51:00,167 --> 01:51:01,634
[Doorbell Buzzes]

1129
01:51:12,346 --> 01:51:14,314
[Spanish]

1130
01:51:20,887 --> 01:51:22,787
Gracias.

1131
01:51:24,891 --> 01:51:26,791
[Door Closes]

1132
01:51:31,231 --> 01:51:34,860
- Creasy.
- Samuel.

1133
01:51:34,968 --> 01:51:36,959
[Lisa]
Honey?

1134
01:51:40,574 --> 01:51:42,940
What's going on?

1135
01:51:44,778 --> 01:51:48,771
That's what I wanna know.
What is going on?

1136
01:51:51,251 --> 01:51:54,152
Huh, Sam?

1137
01:51:54,254 --> 01:51:56,484
I'm gonna ask your wife a couple
of questions, okay?

1138
01:51:56,590 --> 01:51:59,525
You move...

1139
01:51:59,626 --> 01:52:01,594
you make one sound...

1140
01:52:01,695 --> 01:52:04,789
I'll snatch the life right outta you,
you understand?

1141
01:52:04,898 --> 01:52:07,731
[Panting]

1142
01:52:12,105 --> 01:52:14,801
What happened, Lisa, hmm?

1143
01:52:14,941 --> 01:52:16,841
Were you in on this?

1144
01:52:16,943 --> 01:52:21,107
- Or was it just your husband, huh?
- Am I in on what?

1145
01:52:21,214 --> 01:52:24,741
You know what I'm talking about... Pita's
kidnapping, her death. Were you a part of it?

1146
01:52:24,851 --> 01:52:28,150
- Pita got killed because the ransom got stolen.
- Shut up!

1147
01:52:29,689 --> 01:52:32,055
Yeah, the money was stolen.
You're right. He's right.

1148
01:52:32,159 --> 01:52:35,686
The money was stolen by Victor Fuentes.
How much was stolen though, huh?

1149
01:52:35,796 --> 01:52:38,788
- $2.5 million, right?
- What are you talking about?

1150
01:52:38,899 --> 01:52:42,027
He knows what I'm talking about.
$2.5 million. That's what Victor got, isn't it?

1151
01:52:42,135 --> 01:52:45,127
- What are you talking about?
- 2.5 million.

1152
01:52:45,238 --> 01:52:47,536
2.5 million to your lawyer
Jordan Kalfus...

1153
01:52:47,674 --> 01:52:50,768
that he put in an account in the Cayman
Islands, but he won't get a chance to spend it.

1154
01:52:54,147 --> 01:52:56,479
What happened to the other five, Sam?

1155
01:52:56,583 --> 01:52:59,518
Huh? That's 2.5, 2.5.
What is five from 10?

1156
01:52:59,619 --> 01:53:02,087
That's five. What happened
to the other five, Sam? Tell your wife.

1157
01:53:02,189 --> 01:53:04,623
- It's your chance to talk.
What happened to the other five?

1158
01:53:04,724 --> 01:53:06,089
- You got a wife, Creasy?
- No, I don't have a wife.

1159
01:53:06,193 --> 01:53:08,957
Then you'll never know how hard
it could be to tell your wife the truth.

1160
01:53:09,062 --> 01:53:11,292
No, you have a wife!
You tell me what happened!

1161
01:53:11,398 --> 01:53:13,525
It was in this room
that my father prayed.

1162
01:53:13,633 --> 01:53:16,329
- I don't give a fuck about your fucking father!
- My father prayed.

1163
01:53:16,436 --> 01:53:20,338
He prayed that his gambling
debts and his infidelities would
be forgiven right in this room.

1164
01:53:20,440 --> 01:53:23,136
- Samuel! I love you!
- What, Lisa?

1165
01:53:23,276 --> 01:53:27,076
- Tell me the truth.
- I didn't inherit a kingdom! That's the truth!

1166
01:53:27,180 --> 01:53:30,081
You wanna know the truth?
I inherited his debt and his mess.

1167
01:53:30,183 --> 01:53:33,084
- I inherited his lawyerJordan...
- You tell me what happened to my baby!

1168
01:53:33,186 --> 01:53:35,746
Say it! Say it! Say it!

1169
01:53:35,856 --> 01:53:38,484
Say it! Say it! Be a fucking man!

1170
01:53:42,295 --> 01:53:44,729
Jordan told me she'd sit in a room...

1171
01:53:44,831 --> 01:53:47,231
and watch cartoons all day...

1172
01:53:47,334 --> 01:53:50,201
and she'd eat ice cream
and we'd have her back in two days.

1173
01:53:50,303 --> 01:53:52,897
He lied to me!

1174
01:53:53,006 --> 01:53:55,873
That's why he's fucking dead!
I did it!

1175
01:53:56,009 --> 01:53:58,034
I did it, Lisa!

1176
01:53:58,178 --> 01:54:00,840
I agreed to the kidnapping.

1177
01:54:00,947 --> 01:54:04,383
I did it for us...
for the three of us.

1178
01:54:12,826 --> 01:54:14,953
I'm so sorry, Lisa.

1179
01:54:18,331 --> 01:54:20,856
[Lisa Shuddering]

1180
01:54:20,967 --> 01:54:22,935
You kill him.

1181
01:54:24,337 --> 01:54:26,237
You kill him or I will.

1182
01:54:56,636 --> 01:54:58,604
Huh. You know, they say a, um...

1183
01:55:00,974 --> 01:55:04,068
a bullet always tells the truth.

1184
01:55:13,386 --> 01:55:15,354
It never lies.

1185
01:55:28,335 --> 01:55:32,601
- It didn't work for me, Samuel, but maybe...
- [Shudders]

1186
01:55:34,908 --> 01:55:37,433
maybe it'll work for you.

1187
01:55:46,786 --> 01:55:49,380
I'll pray for you.

1188
01:56:01,501 --> 01:56:03,332
[Sniffles]

1189
01:56:26,926 --> 01:56:29,224
[Gunshot]

1190
01:57:25,952 --> 01:57:28,750
[Man Speaking Spanish]

1191
01:58:01,388 --> 01:58:04,846
[Manzano Continues]

1192
01:58:21,775 --> 01:58:24,175
[Chuckles]

1193
01:58:51,805 --> 01:58:53,705
- Gracias.
- [Gunshot]

1194
01:58:55,141 --> 01:58:57,871
[Gasping]

1195
01:58:58,011 --> 01:59:00,912
[Spanish]

1196
01:59:06,085 --> 01:59:08,178
[Exhales, Panting]

1197
01:59:13,193 --> 01:59:16,162
[Phone Ringing]

1198
01:59:18,465 --> 01:59:20,365
- [Mariana] ¿Hola?
- [Creasy] Hola.

1199
01:59:20,467 --> 01:59:22,958
- Mr. Creasy?
- Yeah, it's me.

1200
01:59:23,069 --> 01:59:27,130
- I traced the PIN for you
and I have an address.
- Yeah?

1201
01:59:27,240 --> 01:59:30,698
The cardholder is Reina Rosas Sanchez,
the wife of"The Voice."

1202
01:59:30,844 --> 01:59:35,110
She lives in Los Arcos,
apartment 26D, Via Appia.

1203
01:59:35,215 --> 01:59:37,683
- Good.
- And another thing.

1204
01:59:37,784 --> 01:59:41,584
Pick up today's paper and you'll have
a picture of"The Voice."

1205
01:59:41,688 --> 01:59:43,656
Good. Thank you.

1206
01:59:44,691 --> 01:59:48,627
[Church Bell Ringing]

1207
02:00:43,383 --> 02:00:46,614
[Boy Shouting In Spanish]

1208
02:00:46,719 --> 02:00:48,812
[Creasy]
Shh, shh, shh.

1209
02:00:55,061 --> 02:00:58,224
[Woman Speaking Spanish Over Radio]

1210
02:01:28,895 --> 02:01:32,524
[Baby Crying]

1211
02:01:52,285 --> 02:01:54,219
José? ¿Qué te pasa?

1212
02:01:55,421 --> 02:01:58,413
[Creasy Speaking Spanish]

1213
02:02:00,727 --> 02:02:02,627
[Grunts]

1214
02:02:02,729 --> 02:02:06,290
[Woman Shouting]

1215
02:02:12,972 --> 02:02:15,532
[Tires Screeching]

1216
